## CRITICAL REQUIREMENTS - Enterprise Kubernetes Standards

### 1. Namespace & RBAC (CIS 5.1)
**MUST:**
- Deploy to dedicated namespace (never default)
- Implement RBAC with least privilege
- Use ServiceAccounts with limited permissions
- Disable automountServiceAccountToken unless required
- Network isolation between namespaces

### 2. Pod Security Standards (PSS - Restricted Profile)
**MUST:**
- Enforce restricted pod security standard
- Run as non-root user (runAsNonRoot: true)
- Drop all capabilities, add only required
- Set read-only root filesystem
- Disable privilege escalation
- Set seccomp profile (RuntimeDefault or Localhost)
- Use AppArmor or SELinux

**Security Context Example:**
```yaml
securityContext:
  runAsNonRoot: true
  runAsUser: 10001
  runAsGroup: 10001
  fsGroup: 10001
  seccompProfile:
    type: RuntimeDefault
  capabilities:
    drop:
      - ALL
  readOnlyRootFilesystem: true
  allowPrivilegeEscalation: false
```

### 3. Resource Management (QoS Guaranteed)
**MUST:**
- Set resource requests = limits for critical workloads
- Define CPU and memory limits
- Use Vertical Pod Autoscaler for right-sizing
- Implement Horizontal Pod Autoscaler for scaling
- Set PodDisruptionBudget for availability
- Define ResourceQuota per namespace

### 4. Health & Readiness Probes
**MUST:**
- Implement liveness probe (restart unhealthy pods)
- Implement readiness probe (route traffic when ready)
- Implement startup probe for slow-starting apps
- Use appropriate probe mechanisms (httpGet, exec, tcpSocket, grpc)
- Set proper timeouts and thresholds

### 5. Networking & Service Mesh
**MUST:**
- Define NetworkPolicy for ingress/egress control
- Use Services for pod discovery
- Implement Ingress with TLS
- Consider Service Mesh (Istio, Linkerd) for mTLS
- Use DNS-based service discovery

### 6. Configuration & Secrets Management
**MUST:**
- Use ConfigMaps for non-sensitive configuration
- Use Secrets for sensitive data (encrypted at rest)
- Consider external secrets management (Vault, AWS Secrets Manager)
- Mount secrets as volumes (not environment variables)
- Rotate secrets regularly
- Never hardcode credentials

### 7. Observability & Monitoring
**MUST:**
- Add Prometheus metrics annotations
- Implement structured logging (JSON)
- Use distributed tracing (OpenTelemetry)
- Define ServiceMonitor for Prometheus Operator
- Set up alerts for critical metrics
- Implement audit logging

### 8. High Availability & Reliability
**MUST:**
- Run minimum 3 replicas for production
- Use PodAntiAffinity for zone distribution
- Implement PodDisruptionBudget
- Define proper graceful shutdown (terminationGracePeriodSeconds)
- Handle SIGTERM properly in application
- Use Rolling Update strategy with proper timing

